    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-08T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="596"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.6261/37: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-08T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 8, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>831. A member of the German Embassy states that in accord with an agreement with
                    the Soviet Government the German Government has sent a Consul General to
                    Leningrad and is sending Consuls to Batum and Vladivostok.<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d596fn19">A German Consulate General was established at Vladivostok
                        previous to that established by the American Government. For correspondence
                        concerning establishment of the American Consulate General, see <ref
                            target="frus1940v03#pg_460">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, pp.
                            460</ref> ff.</note> The informant added that for the time being the
                    opening of Consulates in Baku, Odessa and other places is not being considered.
                    The Soviet Government, it is understood, is opening consular offices in Vienna,
                    Hamburg and Koenigsberg.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
